# I/O Scheduler Tuning Rules
# Optimizes I/O performance for different device types
# Imported from EndeavourOS standards

# SSD: no iosched tuning here. 60-io-scheduler.rules sets non-rotating sd*/mmcblk
# disks to mq-deadline, whose defaults already suit SSDs.

# NVMe: Reduce polling delay for responsiveness
ACTION=="add|change", KERNEL=="nvme[0-9]*n[0-9]*", \
  ATTR{queue/io_poll_delay}="0"

# HDD: no iosched tuning here. 60-io-scheduler.rules sets rotating sd* disks to
# BFQ, and BFQ exposes no fifo_batch (that is an mq-deadline tunable), so any
# queue/iosched/fifo_batch write would silently no-op. BFQ defaults suit HDDs.

# Note: read_ahead_kb rules removed - attribute only exists on block devices, not partitions
